    I understand you want to copy the entire app, but this project has over 50 files including frontend, backend, database schemas, and configurations. Putting everything in one code block wouldn't be practical to copy.

    Here are much easier options:

    Option 1: Download from Replit (Easiest)
    1. Click the three dots (...) menu in the top left of your Replit workspace
    2. Select "Download as zip"
    3. This gives you all the code in one download
    Option 2: Use Git

    If your new project supports Git, you can clone this repository directly.

    Option 3: Fork This Repl

    If you're staying on Replit, you can Fork this project to create a copy you can modify.

    Would you like me to help you with any of these options? Or if you have a specific new platform in mind (like a local development setup, or another hosting service), I can give you specific instructions for that.
